<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,906,1183]" pageId="14" pageNumber="61">
This genus was revised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Andersen" box="[463,653,906,931]" pageId="14" pageNumber="61" refString="Andersen, N. M. (1980) Hygropetric water striders of the genus Onychotrechus Kirkaldy with description of a related genus (Insecta, Hemiptera, Gerridae). Steenstrupia, 6, 113 - 146." type="journal article" year="1980">
Andersen (
<number box="[587,645,907,931]" pageId="14" pageNumber="61" value="1980.0">1980</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and was represented by nine described and one undescribed species distributed from 
<collectingCountry box="[338,396,942,967]" name="India" pageId="14" pageNumber="61">India</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[430,536,942,967]" name="Malaysia" pageId="14" pageNumber="61">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
. Of these, only three occur in Southeast Asia. Moreover, the undescribed species was later discovered to be a variation of 
<taxonomicName authority="Andersen" authorityName="Andersen" box="[643,869,978,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Onychotrechus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="esakii">
<collectingCountry box="[643,663,979,1002]" name="Iceland" pageId="14" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis box="[643,663,979,1002]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="61">O</emphasis>
</collectingCountry>
. 
<emphasis box="[682,747,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="61">esakii</emphasis>
Andersen
</taxonomicName>
, which is a common and widespread species in Southeast Asia. Later, one species from 
<collectingCountry box="[604,714,1014,1039]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="14" pageNumber="61">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Polhemus" box="[729,1050,1014,1039]" pageId="14" pageNumber="61" refString="Polhemus, J. T. &amp; Andersen, N. M. (1984) A revision of Amemboa Esaki with notes on the phylogeny and ecological evolution of eotrechine water striders (Insecta, Hemiptera, Gerridae). Steenstrupia, 10, 65 - 111." type="journal article" year="1984">
Polhemus &amp; Andersen 
<number box="[993,1050,1015,1039]" pageId="14" pageNumber="61" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and another from 
<collectingCountry box="[1267,1325,1014,1039]" name="India" pageId="14" pageNumber="61">India</collectingCountry>
(Zettel &amp; Tran 
<number box="[214,272,1051,1075]" pageId="14" pageNumber="61" value="2007.0">2007</number>
) were described. In 
<collectingCountry box="[515,617,1050,1075]" name="Thailand" pageId="14" pageNumber="61">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, only one described species has been recorded (
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[1183,1424,1050,1075]" pageId="14" pageNumber="61" refString="Chen, P. - P. &amp; Zettel, H. (1998) Key to genera and subgenera of Gerridae (Gerromorpha) of Thailand and adjacent countries, with a check-list of species known from Thailand. Amemboa, 2, 24 - 41." type="journal article" year="1998">
Chen &amp; Zettel 
<number box="[1364,1424,1051,1075]" pageId="14" pageNumber="61" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Members of this genus are hygrophilic and found on wet rocks or moss in streams, and some are on the ground away from water but near the aquatic habitat, which is a unique behavior of the genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Andersen" box="[1186,1367,1122,1147]" pageId="14" pageNumber="61" refString="Andersen, N. M. (1980) Hygropetric water striders of the genus Onychotrechus Kirkaldy with description of a related genus (Insecta, Hemiptera, Gerridae). Steenstrupia, 6, 113 - 146." type="journal article" year="1980">
Andersen 
<number box="[1307,1367,1123,1147]" pageId="14" pageNumber="61" value="1980.0">1980</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). One widespread, common species was collected from waterfalls in this study.
</paragraph>
